description:
Two young girls from Amersfoort in the Netherlands, went on a 6 week backpacking trip of a lifetime to Panama. It soon turned into a nightmare & their disappearance has sparked controversy ever since, with multiple theories to what happened to the girls in this bizarre unsolved mystery. 8 years on and many questions remain unanswered. 

We look in depth to the evidence in this cold case, of which there is an abundance. Big credit goes to the people behind imperfectplan.com & Scarlet R from koudekaas.blogspot.com also Juan Perea y Monsuwe (links below) for such thorough investigative skills & dedication in collating the information surrounding the events that resulted in the untimely loss of Kris Kremers, 21 & Lisanne Froon, 22, who were vivacious, gentle souls with promising lives ahead of them. 

For clarity, I would like to point out a mistake I made in commentary, I referred to 77 attempts to call emergency services, this was in fact 77 attempts to unlock the phone, which were unsuccessful. I also want to make it very clear, I do not accuse or attack the tour guide in the video, I just believe he knows more than he eludes to, and I maintain that train of thought. In my opinion, there was human intervention in the girls disappearance, I am in little doubt in regards to that. 

NOT SUITABLE FOR CHILDREN, images of dead bodies & human remains are contained within. No disrespect or insensitivity is intended towards the families & friends of Kris or Lisanne, this was a tragic event that needs to be investigated until the true cause is discovered. Any opinion shared in this video is that of my own, based on research of the evidence. RIP to both, may they never be forgotten.  

Narrated & Created by David Harwood. I originally wrote this in 2020 but due to personal reasons was unable to finish the video, huge thanks to my loyal subscribers, you are all beautiful legends and I sincerely appreciate every one of you.

comments.text: Come on people, Kris and Lisanne just got lost, so lost their bodies exploded and scattered through the jungle, strangely bleached with phosphorus, the same phosphorus used on coffee farms owned by their helpful tour guide who definitely made an appointment with them for 8am April 2nd while simultaneously also never meeting them before. This tour guide was an amateur detective who took it upon himself to search their locked bedroom for half an hour the next morning, which is a totally normal thing to do for no-shows you've never spoken to who couldn't possibly have made this alleged appointment.
